The evidence with the title 'Militia acts of 1792 - Wikipedia ' says The Militia Acts Of 1792 were a pair of statutes enacted by the second United States Congress  ... The first Act , passed may 2, 1792, provided for the authority of the president to call out the militias of the  ... It conscripted every " free able-bodied white male citizen " between the ages of 18 and 45 into a local militia company. 
